{"title":["The State Of The Art In Language Workbenches","the state of the art in language workbenches conclusions from the language workbench challenge"],"author":[{"rawString":"sebastian erdweg"},{"rawString":"tijs van der storm"},{"rawString":"tijs van der storm"},{"rawString":"markus volter"},{"rawString":"meinte boersma"},{"rawString":"remi bosman"},{"rawString":"william r cook"},{"rawString":"albert gerritsen"},{"rawString":"angelo hulshout"},{"rawString":"steven kelly"},{"rawString":"alex loh"},{"rawString":"gabriel d p konat"},{"rawString":"pedro j molina"},{"rawString":"martin palatnik"},{"rawString":"risto pohjonen"},{"rawString":"eugen schindler"},{"rawString":"klemens schindler"},{"rawString":"riccardo solmi"},{"rawString":"vlad vergu"},{"rawString":"eelco visser"},{"rawString":"kevin van der vlist"},{"rawString":"guido wachsmuth"},{"rawString":"jimi van der woning"}],"abstract":["2013 Language workbenches are tools that provide high-level mechanisms for the implementation of (domain-specific) languages. an active area research also receives many contributions from industry. To compare and discuss existing language workbenches, annual Workbench Challenge was launched in 2011. Each year, participants challenged to realize a given domain-specific with their as basis discussion comparison. In this paper, we describe state art observed previous editions Challenge. particular, capture design space feature model show where reside. We these based on DSL questionnaires realized all workbenches."],"numberOfReferences":[65,45,61],"numberOfCitations":[106,49,0],"year":2013,"publisher":["Springer, Cham","Springer International Publishing"],"type":"book-chapter","pdf":["http://homepages.cwi.nl/~storm/publications/lwc13paper.pdf","http://www.student.informatik.tu-darmstadt.de/~xx00seba/publications/language-workbench-state.pdf","http://www.voelter.de/data/pub/LWC13.pdf","https://www.informatik.uni-marburg.de/~seba/publications/language-workbench-state.pdf","https://ww