{"title":["model driven engineering"],"author":[{"rawString":"alberto rodrigues da silva"}],"abstract":["During the last decade a new trend of approaches has emerged, which considers models not just documentation artefacts, but also central artefacts in software engineering field, allowing creation or automatic execution systems starting from those models. These proposals have been classified generically as Model-Driven Engineering (MDE) and share common concepts terms that need to be abstracted, discussed understood. This paper presents survey on MDE based unified conceptual model clearly identifies relates these essential concepts, namely system, model, metamodel, modeling language, transformations, platform, product. In addition, this discusses terminologies relating MDE, MDD, MDA others. is earlier work, however, contrary those, it intends give simple, broader integrated view respective terminology commonly involved answering key questions such as: What model? relation between metamodel? are facets language? How can I use context development process? relations source code platforms? other MD approaches?"],"numberOfReferences":[81],"numberOfCitations":[173],"year":2015,"publisher":["Pergamon"],"type":"Journal article","pdf":["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.cl.2015.06.001","https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2826923","https://core.ac.uk/display/81984327","https://cyberleninka.org/article/n/1262859","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/journals/cl/cl43.html#Silva15","https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1016/j.cl.2015.06.001","https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.cl.2015.06.001","https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1477842415000408","https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Alberto_Silva2/publication/278851131_Model-driven_engineering_A_survey_supported_by_A_unified_conceptual_model/links/559c281a08ae7f3eb4cff75e.pdf"],"uniqueId":[{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1016/J.CL.2015.06.001"},{"type":"MicrosoftAcademic","value":994990881}],"source":["microsoftAcademic"]}
