{"title":["model driven development challenges and solutions experiences with domain specific modelling in industry"],"author":[{"rawString":"juhapekka tolvanen"},{"rawString":"steven kelly"}],"abstract":["Model-Driven Development is reported to succeed the best when modelling based on domain-specific languages. Despite significant benefits MDD has not been applied as widely expected. Costly definition of languages and related generators with tooling, their maintenance domain stable, challenges in scalability, collaboration are some reasons that several studies mention. We believe these statements justifiable but only applying traditional programming tooling for modelling. Instead we show data from practice many can be solved using tools built first place."],"numberOfReferences":[25],"numberOfCitations":[24],"year":2016,"publisher":[],"type":"Conference paper","pdf":["http://dx.doi.org/10.5220/0005833207110719","https://www.metacase.com/papers/Tolvanen_Kelly_MODELSWARD_2016.pdf","http://www.metacase.com/papers/Tolvanen_Kelly_MODELSWARD_2016.pdf","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/modelsward/modelsward2016.html#Tolvanen016","https://doi.org/10.5220/0005833207110719","https://dx.doi.org/10.5220/0005833207110719"],"uniqueId":[{"type":"DOI","value":"10.5220/0005833207110719"},{"type":"MicrosoftAcademic","value":2344283580}],"source":["microsoftAcademic"]}
{"title":["melange a meta language for modular and reusable development of dsls"],"author":[{"rawString":"thomas degueule"},{"rawString":"benoit combemale"},{"rawString":"arnaud blouin"},{"rawString":"olivier barais"},{"rawString":"jeanmarc jezequel"}],"abstract":["Domain-Specific Languages (DSLs) are now developed for a wide variety of domains to address specific concerns in the development complex systems. When engineering new DSLs, it is likely that previous efforts spent on other languages could be leveraged, especially when their overlap. However, legacy DSLs may not fit exactly end user requirements and thus require further extension, restriction, or specialization. While current language workbenches provide import mechanisms, they usually lack an explicit support such customizations imported artifacts. In this paper, we propose approach building by safely assembling customizing This based typing relations reasoning layer manipulating while ensuring type safety. On top layer, algebra operators extending, restricting, separate DSL We implemented into Melange meta-language. illustrate through modular definition executable modeling Internet Of Things domain. show how eases maximizing reuse artifacts without introducing issues terms performance, technical ecosystem compatibility, generated code volume."],"numberOfReferences":[47],"numberOfCitations":[58],"year":2015,"publisher":["ACM"],"type":"Conference paper","pdf":["https://hal.inria.fr/hal-01197038/document","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/sle/sle2015.html#DegueuleCBBJ15","https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/2814251.2814252","https://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/hal-01197038","https://hal.inria.fr/hal-01197038"],"uniqueId":[{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1145/2814251.2814252"},{"type":"MicrosoftAcademic","value":2038025292}],"source":["microsoftAcademic"]}
