{"title":["Multi-Purpose Syntax Definition With Sdf3"],"author":[{"rawString":"luis eduardo de souza amorim"},{"rawString":"eelco visser"}],"abstract":["SDF3 is a syntax definition formalism that extends plain context-free grammars with features such as constructor declarations, declarative disambiguation rules, character-level grammars, permissive syntax, layout constraints, formatting templates, placeholder and modular composition. These support the multi-purpose interpretation of definitions, including derivation type schemas for abstract tree representations, scannerless generalized parsing full class error recovery, layout-sensitive parsing, parenthesization formatting, syntactic completion. This paper gives high level overview by means examples provides guide to literature further details."],"numberOfReferences":[66,52],"numberOfCitations":[1,0],"year":2020,"publisher":["Springer"],"type":"Conference paper","pdf":["https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-030-58768-0_1","https://rd.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-030-58768-0_1","https://research.tudelft.nl/en/publications/multi-purpose-syntax-definition-with-sdf3","https://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1007%2F978-3-030-58768-0_1.pdf"],"uniqueId":[{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1007/978-3-030-58768-0_1"},{"type":"MicrosoftAcademic","value":3084535761},{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1007/978-3-030-58768-0_1"}],"source":["microsoftAcademic","openCitations"],"sourceTitle":"Software Engineering And Formal Methods - Lecture Notes In Computer Science"}
