{"title":["centaur the system"],"author":[{"rawString":"p borras"},{"rawString":"dominique clement"},{"rawString":"th despeyroux"},{"rawString":"janet incerpi"},{"rawString":"gilles kahn"},{"rawString":"bernard lang"},{"rawString":"v pascual"}],"abstract":["This paper describes the organization of CENTAUR system and its main components. The is a generic interactive environment. When given formal specification particular programming language-including syntax semantics — it produces language specific resulting environment includes structure editor, an interpreter/debugger other tools, all which have graphic interfaces. made three parts: database component, that provides standardized representation access to objects their persistent storage; logical engine used execute specifications; object-oriented man-machine interface gives easy system's functions. essentially written in Lisp (Le_Lisp). Prolog (Mu-Prolog). built on top virtual graphics facility Le_Lisp, itself primarily implemented X-Windows."],"numberOfReferences":[17],"numberOfCitations":[341],"year":1988,"publisher":["ACM"],"type":"Conference paper","pdf":["https://hal.inria.fr/inria-00075774/document","http://portal.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=64135.65005","https://core.ac.uk/display/24360918","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/sde/sde88.html#BorrasCDIKLP88","https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/64135.65005","https://doi.org/10.1145/64135.65005","https://hal.inria.fr/inria-00075774","https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=64135.65005","https://doi.acm.org/10.1145/64140.65005"],"uniqueId":[{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1145/64135.65005"},{"type":"MicrosoftAcademic","value":2005915144}],"source":["microsoftAcademic"]}
{"title":["cedalion a language for language oriented programming"],"author":[{"rawString":"david h lorenz"},{"rawString":"boaz rosenan"}],"abstract":["Language Oriented Programming (LOP) is a paradigm that puts domain specific programming languages (DSLs) at the center of software development process. Currently, there are three main approaches to LOP: (1) use internal DSLs, implemented as libraries in given host language; (2) external interpreters or compilers an and (3) language workbenches, which integrated environments (IDEs) for defining using DSLs. In this paper, we contribute: (4) novel language-oriented approach LOP While workbenches adapt DSL features overcome some limitations our adapts workbench We introduce Cedalion, featuring static validation projectional editing. To validate present case study Cedalion was used by biologists designing DNA microarray molecular Biology research."],"numberOfReferences":[29],"numberOfCitations":[25],"year":2011,"publisher":["ACM"],"type":"Conference paper","pdf":["http://cedalion.sourceforge.net/oopsla11.pdf","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/oopsla/oopsla2011.html#LorenzR11","https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/2048066.2048123","https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=2048066.2048123"],"uniqueId":[{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1145/2048066.2048123"},{"type":"MicrosoftAcademic","value":2140493799}],"source":["microsoftAcademic"]}
