{"title":["Declaratively Programming The Mobile Web With Mobl"],"author":[{"rawString":"hemelzef"},{"rawString":"vissereelco"}],"abstract":["A new generation of mobile touch devices, such as the iPhone, iPad and Android are equipped with powerful, modern browsers. However, regular websites not optimized for specific fea...","A new generation of mobile touch devices, such as the iPhone, iPad and Android are equipped with powerful, modern browsers. However, regular websites not optimized for specific features constraints these limited screen estate, unreliable Internet access, touch-based interaction patterns, GPS. While recent advances in web technology enable developers to build applications that take advantage unique properties developing exposes a number problems, specifically: required use many loosely coupled languages tool support application code is often verbose imperative. We introduce mobl, language designed declaratively construct applications. Mobl integrates user interface design, styling, data modeling, querying logic into single, unified flexible, expressive, enables early detection errors, has good IDE support."],"numberOfReferences":[13,19,14,24],"numberOfCitations":[10,64,6,0],"year":2011,"publisher":["#N##TAB##TAB#ACM#N##TAB##TAB#PUB27#N##TAB##TAB#New York, NY, USA#N##TAB#","Delft University of Technology, Software Engineering Research Group","Association for Computing Machinery (ACM)"],"type":"journal-article","pdf":["https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/2076021.2048121","https://repository.tudelft.nl/islandora/object/uuid:e5d125ad-1681-4793-9652-701b3c0ab467/datastream/OBJ/download","http://core.ac.uk/display/19486577","http://repository.tudelft.nl/view/ir/uuid:e5d125ad-1681-4793-9652-701b3c0ab467/","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/oopsla/oopsla2011.html#HemelV11","https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/2048066.2048121","https://doi.acm.org/10.1145/2048066.2048121","https://doi.org/10.1145/2048066.2048121","https://research.tudelft.nl/en/publications/declara