{"title":["Bringing Domain-Specific Languages To Digital Forensics"],"author":[{"rawString":"jeroen van den bos"},{"rawString":"tijs van der storm"}],"abstract":["Digital forensics investigations often consist of analyzing large quantities data. The software tools used for such data are constantly evolving to cope with a multiplicity versions and variants formats. This process customization is time consuming error prone. To improve this situation we present Derric, domain-specific language (DSL) declaratively specifying structures. way, the specification structure separated from processing. resulting architecture encourages facilitates reuse. It enables faster development through division labour between investigators engineers. We have performed an initial evaluation Derric by constructing recovery tool. so-called carver has been automatically derived declarative description JPEG files. compare it existing carvers, show be in same league both respect recovered evidence, runtime performance."],"numberOfReferences":[26,31],"numberOfCitations":[29,13,0],"year":2011,"publisher":["ACM"],"type":"proceedings-article","pdf":["https://homepages.cwi.nl/~storm/publications/dsls-forensics.pdf","http://portal.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=1985793.1985887","http://yadda.icm.edu.pl/yadda/element/bwmeta1.element.ieee-000006032508","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/icse/icse2011.html#BosS11","https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/1985793.1985887","https://doi.org/10.1145/1985793.1985887","https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/6032508/","https://www.narcis.nl/publication/RecordID/oai%3Acwi.nl%3A17358","https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=1985887","https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1145/1985793.1985887"],"uniqueId":[{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1145/1985793.1985887"},{"type":"MicrosoftAcademic","value":2118383482},{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1145/1985793.1985887"},{"type":"ISSN"},{"type":"ISBN","value":["9781450304450"]},{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1145/1985793.1985887"}],"source":["microsoftAcademic","open