{"title":["A Meta-Environment For Generating Programming Environments"],"author":[{"rawString":"paul klint"}],"abstract":["Over the last decade, considerable progress has been made in solving problems of automatic generation programming/development environments, given a formal definition some programming or specification language. In most cases, research focused on functionality and efficiency generated and, course, these aspects will ultimately determine acceptance environment generators. However, only marginal attention paid to development process language definitions itself. Assuming that quality automatically environments be satisfactory within few years, costs then become next limiting factor determining ultimate success generators.In this paper we describe design implementation meta-environment (a for definitions) based formalism ASF + SDF. This is currently being implemented as part Centaur system is, at least partly, obtained by applying techniques A central problem providing fully interactive editing modular such modifications during can translated immediately from original definition. Therefore, issues addressed are treatment formalisms with user-definable syntax incremental program techniques."],"numberOfReferences":[29,5,31],"numberOfCitations":[277,113,0],"year":1993,"publisher":["ACM","Association for Computing Machinery (ACM)"],"type":"journal-article","pdf":["https://doi.acm.org/10.1145/151257.151260","http://dare.uva.nl/document/2/34928","https://pure.uva.nl/ws/files/3383380/34928_157148y.pdf","https://dare.uva.nl/record/1/151564","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/journals/tosem/tosem2.html#Klint93","https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/151257.151260","https://doi.org/10.1145/151257.151260","https://www.narcis.nl/publication/RecordID/oai%3Adare.uva.nl%3Apublications%2Fde2af6fe-9079-4761-bc61-12aef8af0231","https://ir.cwi.nl/pub/5651/5651.pdf","https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1145/151257.151260"],"uniqueId":[{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1145/151257.151260"},{"type"