{"title":["RASCAL: A Domain Specific Language for Source Code Analysis and Manipulation"],"author":[{"rawString":"paul klint"},{"rawString":"tijs van der storm"},{"rawString":"jurgen vinju"}],"abstract":["Many automated software engineering tools require tight integration of techniques for source code analysis and manipulation. State-of-the-art exist both, but the domains have remained notoriously separate because different computational paradigms fit each domain best. This impedance mismatch hampers development new solutions desired functionality scalability can only be achieved by repeated ad hoc techniques. Rascal is a domain-specific language that takes away most this boilerplate integrating manipulation at conceptual, syntactic, semantic technical level. We give an overview assess its merits implementing complex refactoring."],"numberOfReferences":[21,14,19],"numberOfCitations":[240,105],"year":2009,"publisher":["IEEE"],"type":"proceedings-article","pdf":["https://doi.org/10.1109/SCAM.2009.28","http://www.cs.kent.edu/~jmaletic/cs63902/Papers/Klint-scam-09.pdf","https://homepages.cwi.nl/~paulk/publications/rascal-scam-09.pdf","https://ir.cwi.nl/pub/15097/15097A.pdf","http://www.narcis.nl/publication/RecordID/oai%3Acwi.nl%3A15097","http://yadda.icm.edu.pl/yadda/element/bwmeta1.element.ieee-000005279910","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/scam/scam2009.html#KlintSV09","https://dx.doi.org/10.1109/SCAM.2009.28","https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/5279910/","https://ir.cwi.nl/pub/15097","http://www.cwi.nl/~paulk/publications/rascal-scam-09.pdf","http://xplorestaging.ieee.org/ielx5/5279860/5279861/05279910.pdf?arnumber=5279910"],"uniqueId":[{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1109/SCAM.2009.28"},{"type":"MicrosoftAcademic","value":2104789737},{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1109/scam.2009.28"},{"type":"ISSN"},{"type":"ISBN","value":["9780769537931"]},{"type":"DOI","value":"10.1109/scam.2009.28"}],"source":["microsoftAcademic","openCitations","crossRef"],"sourceTitle":"2009 Ninth Ieee International Working Conference On Source Code Analysis And Manipulation"}
{"title":["Mbeddr: Instantiating A Language Workbench In The Embedded Software Domain"],"author":[{"rawString":"markus voelter"},{"rawString":"daniel ratiu"},{"rawString":"bernd kolb"},{"rawString":"bernhard schaetz"}],"abstract":["Tools can boost software developer productivity, but building custom tools is prohibitively expensive, especially for small organizations. For example, embedded programmers often have to use low-level C with limited IDE support, and integrated into an off-the-shelf tool chain in ad-hoc way. To address these challenges, we built mbeddr, extensible language development based on C. mbeddr a large-scale instantiation of the Jetbrains MPS workbench. Exploiting its capabilities modularization composition, projectional editing multi-stage transformation, open modular framework that lets third parties add extensions minimal effort without invasive changes. End users combine programs as needed. illustrate approach, this paper discuss mbeddr’s support state machines, components, decision tables, requirements tracing, product line variability program verification outline their implementation. We also present our experience which shows relying workbenches dramatically reduces customized, languages IDEs point where affordable by Finally, report using commercial project, illustrates benefits end users."],"numberOfReferences":[76,29,78],"numberOfCitations":[54,32,0],"year":2013,"publisher":["Springer US","Springer Science and Business Media LLC"],"type":"journal-article","pdf":["https://doi.org/10.1007/s10515-013-0120-4","http://mbeddr.com/files/voelteretal-mbeddr-final.pdf","https://www.voelter.de/data/pub/voelteretal-mbeddr-AUSE.pdf","http://www.voelter.de/data/pub/voelteretal-mbeddr-AUSE.pdf","https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/journals/ase/ase20.html#VoelterRKS13","https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs10515-013-0120-4","http://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1007/s10515-013-0120-4.pdf","http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10515-013-0120-4/f